  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It looks like for some reason the docker image isn't taking my `engine-jwt-secret` setting...\r\n\r\nRunning:\r\n`hyperledger/besu:latest`\r\n`704f9b0044e79cce6008633189bbc578db8fe56c6a1716012c02a826d5e3fc64`\r\n\r\nIn docker-compose (trimmed for simplicity):\r\n```\r\n    volumes:\r\n        - /data/volumes/besu/data:/data\r\n    command:\r\n      - --data-path=/data\r\n      - --engine-rpc-port=8552\r\n      - --engine-jwt-secret=/data/jwtsecret\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn volume on host:\r\n```\r\n# ls /data/volumes/besu/data/\r\nbesu.networks  besu.ports  caches  database  DATABASE_METADATA.json  fastsync  jwt.hex  key\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn docker logs:\r\n```\r\n# docker-compose up -d && docker logs --tail 10 -f besu\r\nRecreating besu ... done\r\n2022-08-31 01:49:26.318+00:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using LibEthPairings native alt bn128\r\n2022-08-31 01:49:26.320+00:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Using the native implementation of the signature algorithm\r\n2022-08-31 01:49:26.322+00:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Starting Besu version: besu/MysticRyuujin-besu/v22.7.1/linux-x86_64/openjdk-java-11\r\n2022-08-31 01:49:26.509+00:00 | main | INFO  | Besu | Engine API authentication enabled without key file. Expect ephemeral jwt.hex file in datadir\r\n```\r\n\r\nI know that the rest of my flags are working and being read... the line before `engine-jwt-secret` I have `- --engine-rpc-port=8552` and the logs reflect this:\r\n```\r\n2022-08-31 01:56:38.379+00:00 | vert.x-eventloop-thread-1 | INFO  | JsonRpcService | JSON-RPC service started and listening on 0.0.0.0:8552\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo it's reading all other flags just fine, but for some reason it doesn't like `- --engine-jwt-secret=/data/jwtsecret`",
